{"id":17598,"title":"DNA extraction from avian faeces stored in ethanol","title_html":"DNA extraction from avian faeces stored in ethanol","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png"},"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.ve6e3he","doi_status":2,"uri":"dna-extraction-from-avian-faeces-stored-in-ethanol-ve6e3he","type_id":1,"template_id":1,"published_on":1591358200,"parent_protocols":[],"parent_collections":[],"cited_protocols":[],"version_id":0,"created_on":1541671832,"categories":null,"creator":{"name":"James Nicholls","affiliation":"CSIRO","affiliations":[{"affiliation":"CSIRO","url":"","is_default":1}],"username":"james-nicholls","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/015.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/015.png"},"badges":[{"id":2,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/bronze.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/bronze.svg"},"name":"Author"}],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"article_citation":null,"public":1,"has_versions":0,"link":null,"total_collections":0,"number_of_steps":19,"authors":[{"name":"James Nicholls","affiliation":"University of Edinburgh","affiliations":[],"username":"james-nicholls","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/015.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/015.png"},"badges":[],"verified":1,"is_verified_user":true,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"is_owner":1,"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"can_claim_authorship":0,"can_accept_authorship":0,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":1,"fork_id":null,"url":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/view\/dna-extraction-from-avian-faeces-stored-in-ethanol-ve6e3he","forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":0,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"guid":"86B6A95FB9DA11E99CA40242AC110005","state_version_id":0,"steps":[{"id":736299,"guid":"DCF98D306B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"38B729B890FB4F79987FD319247FBCC7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0C6869D7F83A4962827F89F225802D49","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove ~100-200 mg of blue tit faeces (typically 2-3 small fragments of faeces, each ~5 mm long) from storage tube, allow ethanol to evaporate off, and then place into a 2 mL round-bottomed centrifuge tube (Eppendorf 2 mL SafeLock tubes are good).  Avoid using faeces that has lots of uric acid on it, or scrape off uric acid.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736300,"guid":"DD076FE06B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736299,"previous_guid":"DCF98D306B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4DAA6D877AF345F2B3101EB6AF309DFD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C26DEA3CF89F4256A4E1CC173A1B9AFE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1.4 mL Buffer ASL to the faecal sample. Vortexing will not typically homogenise dried avian faeces, so to homogenise add one 3 mm diameter tungsten carbide bead and shake on a Qiagen TissueLyser for 1 minute at 24 Hz.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736301,"guid":"DD0796F06B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736300,"previous_guid":"DD076FE06B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"84FED158875D4CBF8851C03D9100A37F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"659FB985EC3445369F0C257AFA536D4F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 20 uL of Proteinase K (using stock supplied in Stool kit).  Vortex briefly to mix, then heat the suspension for 30 minutes at 70 \u00b0C.  Both adding ProtK at this step and homogenising using the TissueLyser in the previous step increase DNA yields.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736302,"guid":"DD0796F16B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736301,"previous_guid":"DD0796F06B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"29414FB78E10476A948CDCE365A1955D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"85FFA8BAFA544E8280FA2CAAA0E577AA","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Vortex for 30 seconds, then centrifuge sample at 13,000 rpm for 1 minute to pellet faecal particles.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736303,"guid":"DD0796F26B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736302,"previous_guid":"DD0796F16B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"CE9B9A4F91F5494C82AEE041E272C575","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5D8BE89DD3DC4018943B0F3674BF3A1E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Pipet 1.2 mL of the supernatant into a new 2 mL centrifuge tube.  The remaining faecal material can be stored and used for microscopic analysis if required; otherwise discard the pellet but don\u2019t forget to retrieve tungsten carbide bead first.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736304,"guid":"DD07BE006B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736303,"previous_guid":"DD0796F26B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E7B201ACEBA7418DA4B9F6E2A6B7AE66","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8492E6FB694D4904B57C5DFEA61B4544","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1 InhibitEX tablet to the sample and vortex immediately and continuously for 1 minute or until the tablet is completely suspended.  Incubate suspension for 1 minute at room temperature to allow inhibitors to absorb to the InhibitEX matrix.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736305,"guid":"DD07BE016B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736304,"previous_guid":"DD07BE006B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1C8489CE0F7744CAA4E9B6537C8621CA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2157E818048E415999CA8D468825EF05","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge sample at 13,000 rpm for 3 minutes to pellet inhibitors bound to InhibitEX matrix.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736306,"guid":"DD07BE026B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736305,"previous_guid":"DD07BE016B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"CB7922A933DB40F1A6A564B0654686B5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6DCCD8788176424D8D982B60FD6D5146","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Pipet all the supernatant (typically 400-600 \u03bcL) into a new 1.5 mL centrifuge tube and discard the pellet.  Centrifuge the sample at full speed for 3 minutes.  Transfer of small quantities of pellet material will not affect the procedure.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736307,"guid":"DD07BE036B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736306,"previous_guid":"DD07BE026B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E2DE08881BD0444B84335BED38CBADA3","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BF4DDE6FCAF549C5B8831EFB00FAC8C5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Pipet 20 \u03bcL of Proteinase K (either from kit, or a user-supplied 10mg\/mL solution) into a new 1.5 mL centrifuge tube.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736308,"guid":"DD54F3A06B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736307,"previous_guid":"DD07BE036B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B9C6287C4BE7437F9CC4A9E6A470C261","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FF63CD89E3DB447BB10CADA337620DF0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Pipet 400 \u03bcL of supernatant from step 8 into the 1.5 mL tube containing proteinase K.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736309,"guid":"DD6B13B06B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736308,"previous_guid":"DD54F3A06B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C3747F7560FE4120ABCE11F4955C4F20","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"744A31D4B93B45D88F58B911F2476B52","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 400 \u03bcL of Buffer AL, and mix well by vortexing for 15 seconds.  Don\u2019t add the proteinase K directly to buffer AL.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736310,"guid":"DD6B13B16B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736309,"previous_guid":"DD6B13B06B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"AFF627D18D4D4410AAE90543E6F5F54A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1E48648FD0AC48EFB12DD52D536F7FCA","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Incubate at 70 \u00b0C for 15 minutes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736311,"guid":"DD6B13B26B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736310,"previous_guid":"DD6B13B16B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"FD83F79BFC8D4293A8B1A403C86574E9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"805BC5536168436F8E725EAF017DB2E5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 400 \u03bcL of ethanol (96-100%) to the lysate and mix well by vortexing.  Centrifuge briefly to remove any liquid from the lid of the tube.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736312,"guid":"DD6B3AC06B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736311,"previous_guid":"DD6B13B26B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6305C798D0C746A6AC8CD86222AFA7F9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"149DF5225CB741ECB43AD0B8CC6C8503","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Carefully apply 600 \u03bcL of the lysate to a QIAamp spin column (in a 2 mL collection tube) without moistening the rim.  Centrifuge at 13,000 rpm for 1 minute.  Place spin column in a new 2 mL collection tube and discard the tube containing the filtrate.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736313,"guid":"DD6B3AC16B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736312,"previous_guid":"DD6B3AC06B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"DA8916C5E378404E835AAF7B778118AF","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F5189836DDCA4FFDAA5CA796FF65F6F1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Repeat step 14 using the remaining liquid from step 13.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736314,"guid":"DD6B3AC26B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736313,"previous_guid":"DD6B3AC16B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F5FD6C7E692548908299BA109C3E86C6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"95435B4520CD4D88BF53672D7235D6DD","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Carefully open the spin column and add 500 \u03bcL of Buffer AW1.  Centrifuge at 13,000 rpm for 1 minute.  Place spin column in a new 2 mL collection tube and discard the tube containing the flow-through.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736315,"guid":"DD6B61D06B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736314,"previous_guid":"DD6B3AC26B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E65FC41B68D64ECDA836A6BF7607AE89","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BA28A39AD1CF49AF84421BBF23599238","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Carefully open the spin column and add 500 \u03bcL of Buffer AW2.  Centrifuge at 13,000 rpm for 2 minutes.  Discard tube containing the flow-through.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736316,"guid":"DD6B61D16B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736315,"previous_guid":"DD6B61D06B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"421145D9D92D437682B27063ECE920A1","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3E069198D488410D867AA6E67947F4E3","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Place spin column in a new 2 mL collection tube.  Centrifuge at 13,000 rpm for 1 minute. Discard tube containing flow-through.  This step ensures the silica membrane is completely dry and has no residual ethanol from Buffer AW2.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":736317,"guid":"DDF5A0706B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","previous_id":736316,"previous_guid":"DD6B61D16B3D11E98DC501B59DB9B802","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9CCB3AA44E5B49DDBE4582BA532ACD15","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4AC5353D1A9D40AFB3F312B4AF999FD8","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer the spin column into a new 1.5 mL centrifuge tube.  Using a low-bind tube will minimise DNA loss through adsorption to tube walls (Eppendorf DNA LoBind tubes are good).  Pipet 50 \u03bcL of Buffer EB (not supplied in kit; Buffer EB = 10 mM Tris) directly onto the spin column membrane.  Incubate for 5 minutes at room temperature, then centrifuge at 13,000 rpm for 1 minute to elute DNA.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[{"id":9033,"mol_weight":0,"name":"QIAamp\u00ae Fast DNA Stool Mini Kit ","linfor":"","url":"","sku":"51604","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Qiagen","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.qiagen.com\/us\/products\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":25},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">DNA extraction from blue tit (Cyanistes caeruleus) faeces stored in ethanol.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Methodology uses the Qiagen QIAamp DNA Stool Kit (Qiagen part no. 51504), following the \u201cIsolation of DNA from Stool for Pathogen Detection\u201d protocol (June 2012 edition), with some modifications following Zeale <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">et al<\/span><span>. 2011 (Mol. Ecol. Res. 11: 236-244) and custom modifications to accommodate dried avian faeces.  Custom modifications include homogenisation of samples in lysis buffer by shaking in a TissueLyser with a tungsten carbine bead, increased lysis times in the presence of additional Proteinase K, and use of larger buffer volumes; all these modifications were experimentally validated to improve DNA yields.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1591358200}